==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lambaste
<hw>Lam*baste"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Lam</ets>
+ <ets>baste</ets> to beat.]</ety> <def>To beat severely;</def>
<specif>specifically,</specif> <def>to beat with a cane.</def>
<mark>[Low]</mark> <rj><au>Nares.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> cane, flog, lambaste.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to scold, reprimand, or berate harshly.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rebuke, rag, reproof, reprimand, jaw, dress down,
scold, chide, berate, bawl out, jaw at, remonstrate with, chew out, chew
up, have words with, lambast.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lambative</ent>⟦br⟧
